Responsibility for making an independent legal assessment of an item and securing any necessary permissions ultimately rests with persons desiring to use the item.</p>\n<p>The NEH awardee responsible for producing each digital object is presented in the Chronicling America page display, below the page image  \u2013 e.g. Image produced by the Library of Congress. For more information on current NDNP awardees, see <a href=\"https://www.loc.gov/ndnp/listawardees.html\">https://www.loc.gov/ndnp/listawardees.html</a>.</p>\n<p>For more information on Library of Congress policies and disclaimers regarding rights and reproductions, see <a href=\"https://www.loc.gov/homepage/legal.html\">https://www.loc.gov/homepage/legal.html</a></p>"], "score": 13.655856, "shard": "09", "shelf_id": "sn84036008, 1907-10-29, Edition 1", "site": ["chroniclingamerica"], "source_group": "ndnp/mthi", "source_modified": "2000-01-01T12:00:00Z", "subject": ["newspapers", "united states", "montana", "yellowstone", "billings (mont.)", "billings"], "subject_headings": ["Billings (Mont.)--Newspapers", "Montana--Billings", "United States--Montana--Yellowstone--Billings"], "subjects": [{"billings": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:billings&fo=json"}, {"billings (mont.)": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:billings+%28mont.%29&fo=json"}, {"montana": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:montana&fo=json"}, {"newspapers": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:newspapers&fo=json"}, {"united states": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:united+states&fo=json"}, {"yellowstone": "https://www.loc.gov/search/?fa=subject:yellowstone&fo=json"}], "timestamp": "2023-07-06T10:43:05.276Z", "title": "The Billings gazette (Billings, Mont.), October 29, 1907", "type": ["issue"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/sn84036008/1907-10-29/ed-1/"}, "locations": null, "method": "mets_filesec", "more_like_this": [{"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/sn84036008/", "http://lccn.loc.gov/sn84036008"], "batch": ["mthi_kelseya_ver02"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1896", "description": ["Semiweekly Vol. 11, no. 40 (Jan. 21, 1896)- \"Republican.\" Publisher varies. Archived issues are available in digital format from the Library of Congress Chronicling America online collection. Billings weekly gazette (1919)"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-06-05T18:25:15.450Z", "group": ["newspaper-titles", "ndnp/newspapers", "catalog-split-14", "catalog", "united-states-newspaper-directory", "main-catalog-split-14"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn84036008/", "image_url": [], "index": 5, "language": ["english"], "latlong": [45.78265, -108.504578], "location": ["yellowstone", "montana", "united states", "billings"], "location_str": "", "lonlat": [-108.504578, 45.78265], "number": ["montana hist soc libr", "univ of wyoming libr, newsp proj", "1059", "2372-868x", "2025-06-25t14:22:23", "2026-04-13t21:30:13", "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn84036008/1899-01-03/ed-1/", "sn84036008", "10317615", "http://www.loc.gov/item/sn84036008/1909-12-31/ed-1/", "2025-05-23t21:30:26", "online resource", "1", "microfilm service copy"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["serial and government publications division", "chronicling america", "catalog", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "the billings gazette (billings, mont.) 1896-1919"], "publication_frequency": ["semiweekly"], "score": 61.21457, "shelf_id": "Newspaper", "site": ["chroniclingamerica", "usnd", "catalog"], "subject": ["newspapers", "united states", "montana", "yellowstone", "billings (mont.)", "billings"], "timestamp": "2026-07-18T09:12:23.572Z", "title": "The Billings gazette", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/sn84036008/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2014218350/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1896", "dates": ["[1896 TO 1919]"], "description": ["Semiweekly Began January 21, 1896. \"Republican.\" Publisher: Gazette Printing Company, <January 1-December 31, 1909>. Description based on: Vol. XIV, no. 73 (January 3, 1899); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed May 7, 2014). Latest issue consulted: Vol. XXI, no. 205 (December 31, 1909) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed May 7, 2014). Billings weekly gazette (1919 : Online)"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:25.703Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2014218350/", "image_url": [], "index": 6, "language": ["english"], "location": ["yellowstone", "montana", "united states", "billings"], "number": ["2014218350", "online resource", "879332903", "2372-8698", "2026-04-13t21:30:13"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["serial and government publications division", "the billings gazette (billings, yellowstone county, montana) 1896-1919 [online resource]", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries"], "publication_frequency": ["semiweekly"], "score": 52.100384, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["electronic journals", "periodicals", "newspapers", "united states", "montana", "yellowstone", "billings (mont.)", "billings"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T20:50:11.310Z", "title": "The Billings gazette", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2014218350/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2014218355/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1918", "dates": ["[1918 TO 1929]"], "description": ["Weekly <Oct. 9-30, 1922> Began with volume 2, number 8 (October 19, 1918). Ceased in 1922? Last issue located: Vol. 5, no. 8 [i.e. 9] (Oct. 30, 1922). Place of publication varies: Great Falls, Oct. 19, 1918-May 7, 1921; Billings, June 10-<Oct. 30>, 1922. Suspended: Nov. 16-23, 1918; June 1921-May 1922. Official organ of: National Nonpartisan League in the State of Montana. Description based on: Volume 2, number 8 (October 19, 1918); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed May 7, 2014). Latest issue consulted: Volume 3, number 51 (December 20, 1919) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed May 7, 2014)."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:25.703Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2014218355/", "image_url": [], "index": 7, "language": ["english"], "location": ["united states", "montana", "yellowstone", "cascade", "billings", "great falls"], "number": ["2014218355", "2372-8884", "2026-04-13t21:30:13", "879345154", "online resource"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["the montana nonpartisan (great falls, montana) 1918-192? [online resource]", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "serial and government publications division"], "publication_frequency": ["weekly"], "score": 52.100384, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["newspapers", "united states", "montana", "national nonpartisan league", "great falls (mont.)", "yellowstone", "billings (mont.)", "cascade", "billings", "great falls"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T20:50:11.310Z", "title": "The Montana nonpartisan", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2014218355/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2015270771/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1882", "dates": ["[1882 TO 1885]"], "description": ["Weekly Began with vol. I, no. 2 (June 1, 1882); ceased with vol. III, no. 49 (May 2, 1885). \"Democratic.\" Cf. An Illustrated history of the Yellowstone Valley. Publisher varies: Devine & McFarlin, <May 2, 1885>. First issue misnumbered no. 2. Cf. An Illustrated history of the Yellowstone Valley. Merged with: Billings rustler, and: Post (Billings, Mont.), to form: Daily gazette (Billings, Mont.), and: Montana stock gazette. Description based on: Vol. 1, no. 2 (June 1, 1882); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed January 13, 2016). Latest issue consulted: Vol. III, no. 49 (May 2, 1885) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed January 13, 2016). Billings rustler Post (Billings, Mont.) Daily gazette (Billings, Mont.) Montana stock gazette"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:33.390Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2015270771/", "image_url": [], "index": 8, "language": ["english"], "location": ["yellowstone", "montana", "united states", "billings"], "number": ["online resource", "934627548", "2470-3265", "2015270771", "2026-04-13t21:30:13"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["the billings herald (billings, montana) 1882-1885 [online resource]", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries", "serial and government publications division"], "publication_frequency": ["weekly"], "score": 52.100384, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["newspapers", "united states", "montana", "yellowstone", "billings (mont.)", "billings"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T20:52:54.074Z", "title": "The Billings herald", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2015270771/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/sn84036001/", "http://lccn.loc.gov/sn84036001"], "batch": ["mthi_harrier_ver01"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1882", "description": ["Weekly Vol. 1, no. 2 (June 1, 1882)-v. 3, no. 49 (May 2, 1885). \"Democratic.\" Cf. An Illustrated history of the Yellowstone Valley. Publisher varies. First issue misnumbered no. 2. Cf. An Illustrated history of the Yellowstone Valley. Archived issues are available in digital format from the Library of Congress Chronicling America online collection. Merged with: Billings rustler, and: Post (Billings, Mont.), to form: Daily gazette (Billings, Mont.), and: Montana stock gazette. Billings rustler (DLC)sn 84036004 Post (Billings, Mont.) (DLC)sn 84036003 Daily gazette (Billings, Mont.) 2576-7097 (DLC)sn 85053069 (OCoLC)11806872 Montana stock gaze